rsCmtsMib.name: rsCmtsMib

revisions.description: First Version of the Riverstone CMTS MIB.

rsCmtsMib.contactinfo: Riverstone Networks, Inc 5200 Great America Parkway Santa Clara CA USA 95054 PHONE:+1 408.878.6500 EMAIL: nms-eng@riverstonenet.com WEB: http://www.riverstonenet.com
rsCmtsMib.description: This mib module defines the Riverstone Networks enterpise MIB for CMTS modules. http://www.riverstonenet.com/products. Copyright (C) Riverstone Networks, Inc 2000

RsCmtsCmdStatus.name: RsCmtsCmdStatus
RsCmtsCmdStatus.description: A unique value for each status code of the generic cmts command variable.

rsCmtsBaseEntry.name: rsCmtsBaseEntry
rsCmtsBaseEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each MAC entry, extending the information in ifEntry. An entry in this table exists for each ifEntry with an ifType of docsCableMaclayer(127).

rsCmtsBaseBpduFilter.name: rsCmtsBaseBpduFilter
rsCmtsBaseBpduFilter.description: Indicates whether we do BPDU filtering on the headend.

rsCmtsBaseBpduFilterHits.name: rsCmtsBaseBpduFilterHits
rsCmtsBaseBpduFilterHits.description: Counts number of BPDU filter hits on the headend.

rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilter.name: rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilter
rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilter.description: Indicates whether we do non-IP filtering on the headend.

rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilterHits.name: rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilterHits
rsCmtsBaseNonIPFilterHits.description: Counts number of non-IP filter hits on the headend.

rsCmtsBaseMapLength.name: rsCmtsBaseMapLength
rsCmtsBaseMapLength.description: Length of the generated maps in microseconds.

rsCmtsBaseMapLeadTime.name: rsCmtsBaseMapLeadTime
rsCmtsBaseMapLeadTime.description: The amount of time between when we send a map and its effective start time in microseconds.

rsCmtsBaseInitMaintLength.name: rsCmtsBaseInitMaintLength
rsCmtsBaseInitMaintLength.description: The length of the initial maintenance interval in microseconds.

rsCmtsBaseConcatenation.name: rsCmtsBaseConcatenation
rsCmtsBaseConcatenation.description: Indicates whether we do Concatenation on the headend.

rsCmtsBaseBpiHwAssist.name: rsCmtsBaseBpiHwAssist
rsCmtsBaseBpiHwAssist.description: Indicates whether we do key generation in hardware.

rsCmtsBaseGenericCmd.name: rsCmtsBaseGenericCmd
rsCmtsBaseGenericCmd.description: A generic command to be applied to the active or startup configuration. The string is not to exceed 255 alpha-numeric characters. To write or check the status of the command, use the variable rsCmtsBaseGenericCmdStatus.

rsCmtsBaseGenericCmdStatus.name: rsCmtsBaseGenericCmdStatus
rsCmtsBaseGenericCmdStatus.description: This variable is used to write the command in rsCmtsBaseGenericCmd to either the active or startup configuration file. It is also useful to determine if the command is written successfully. These are the codes of the status: undefined(0) -- default value active(1) -- write to active configuration startup(2) -- write to startup configuration process(3) -- processing request success(4) -- write succeeded failed(5) -- write failed

rsCmtsBaseUccRetryInterval.name: rsCmtsBaseUccRetryInterval
rsCmtsBaseUccRetryInterval.description: Interval in milliseconds between successive UCC requests.

rsCmtsBaseUccRetries.name: rsCmtsBaseUccRetries
rsCmtsBaseUccRetries.description: Number of UCC request retries before timing out.

rsCmtsUpstreamEntry.name: rsCmtsUpstreamEntry
rsCmtsUpstreamEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each Upstream entry, extending the information in ifEntry.

rsCmtsUpstreamNominalRxPower.name: rsCmtsUpstreamNominalRxPower
rsCmtsUpstreamNominalRxPower.description: The value indicates the nominal, receive power (indBmV) of each upstream RF port.

rsCmtsUpstreamState.name: rsCmtsUpstreamState
rsCmtsUpstreamState.description: Indicates that the given upstream port is operational.

rsCmtsUpstreamPolicing.name: rsCmtsUpstreamPolicing
rsCmtsUpstreamPolicing.description: Indicates if we are doing upstream traffic policing.

rsCmtsUpstreamRangeInterval.name: rsCmtsUpstreamRangeInterval
rsCmtsUpstreamRangeInterval.description: Indicates the Invited (Periodic) Ranging Intervals as input to the Bandwidth Allocator algorithm.

rsCmtsUpstreamRangeRetryInterval.name: rsCmtsUpstreamRangeRetryInterval
rsCmtsUpstreamRangeRetryInterval.description: Indicates the Invited (Periodic) Ranging Retry Intervals as input to the Bandwidth Allocator algorithm.

rsCmtsUpstreamPowerThreshold.name: rsCmtsUpstreamPowerThreshold
rsCmtsUpstreamPowerThreshold.description: Indicates the Power Threshold for the upstream port.

rsCmtsUpstreamPowerAdjust.name: rsCmtsUpstreamPowerAdjust
rsCmtsUpstreamPowerAdjust.description: Indicates whether we override upstream power adjustments performed by the CMTS to the CMs. If set the 'true', all RNG-Resp messages will be transmitted with ZERO power adjustment, regardless of received upstream power levels.

rsCmtsUpstreamTimingAdjust.name: rsCmtsUpstreamTimingAdjust
rsCmtsUpstreamTimingAdjust.description: Indicates whether we override upstream timing adjustments performed by the CMTS to the CMs. If set the 'true', all RNG-Resp messages will be transmitted with ZERO timing adjustment, regardless of received upstream timing.

rsCmtsUpstreamFreqencyAdjust.name: rsCmtsUpstreamFreqencyAdjust
rsCmtsUpstreamFreqencyAdjust.description: Indicates whether we override upstream frequency adjustments performed by the CMTS to the CMs. If set the 'true', all RNG-Resp messages will be transmitted with ZERO frequency adjustment, regardless of received upstream frequency levels.

rsCmtsUpstreamTXCoefficients.name: rsCmtsUpstreamTXCoefficients
rsCmtsUpstreamTXCoefficients.description: Indicates whether we omit the equalization coefficients for this upstream channel.

rsCmtsUpstreamForceContinue.name: rsCmtsUpstreamForceContinue
rsCmtsUpstreamForceContinue.description: Indicates whether we force all RNG-Resp messages to issue a 'Continue' Ranging Status indefinitely.

rsCmtsUpstreamQosConfirm.name: rsCmtsUpstreamQosConfirm
rsCmtsUpstreamQosConfirm.description: Indicates whether we would like to confirm the requested QoS parameters for this upstream during registration.

rsCmtsUpstreamQosMaxBps.name: rsCmtsUpstreamQosMaxBps
rsCmtsUpstreamQosMaxBps.description: The maximum number of bits per second of upstream bandwidth that we will allot to modems which request a minimum upstream rate. We use this to control the amount of bandwidth oversubscription.

rsCmtsModulationTable.name: rsCmtsModulationTable
rsCmtsModulationTable.description: Describes a modulation profile associated with one or more upstream channels.

rsCmtsModulationEntry.name: rsCmtsModulationEntry
rsCmtsModulationEntry.description: Describes a modulation profile for an Interval Usage Code for one or more upstream channels.

rsCmtsModulationUWLength.name: rsCmtsModulationUWLength
rsCmtsModulationUWLength.description: Length of unique word pattern, in bytes.

rsCmtsModulationDetectWindow.name: rsCmtsModulationDetectWindow
rsCmtsModulationDetectWindow.description: Time window around a nominal detection time in which the unique window detector is enabled.

rsCmtsModulationUWMismatch.name: rsCmtsModulationUWMismatch
rsCmtsModulationUWMismatch.description: Specifies precision of match between unique word pattern and incoming burst by specifying the number of bits which are allowed to NOT match.

rsCmtsModulationEQSymbols.name: rsCmtsModulationEQSymbols
rsCmtsModulationEQSymbols.description: Equalizer training sequence length, in symbols.

rsCmtsDownstreamEntry.name: rsCmtsDownstreamEntry
rsCmtsDownstreamEntry.description: An entry containing objects describing attributes of each Downstream entry, extending the information in ifEntry.

rsCmtsDownstreamState.name: rsCmtsDownstreamState
rsCmtsDownstreamState.description: Indicates whether the downstream port is enabled.

rsCmtsDownstreamModulation.name: rsCmtsDownstreamModulation
rsCmtsDownstreamModulation.description: Indicates whether downstream modulation is turned on. When disabled, the downstream transmitter will output a CW, or tonal signal, at the tuned RF frequency.

rsCmtsBaseGroup.name: rsCmtsBaseGroup
rsCmtsBaseGroup.description: A collection of objects providing additional configuration and monitoring capabilites of Cable Modem Line Card parameters.

rsCmtsMibCompliance.name: rsCmtsMibCompliance
rsCmtsMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing Riverstone extended Cable Modem MIB.
